'''Elizabeth Rice Allgeier''' (March 4, 1941 – October 9, 2016) was an American [[psychologist]] and [[sexologist]]. She was the Editor of the ''[[Journal of Sex Research]]'' in the 1990s.<ref>{{cite journal |title= Back Matter |author= |date= |jstor=3813488}}</ref> She was Professor [[Emeritus]] of Psychology at [[Bowling Green State University]]. She joined BGSU in 1980 and retired in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bgsu.edu/offices/mc/monitor/pastissues/06-27-05/emeriti_2005.html|title=A-Z links|website=Bowling Green State University}}</ref> She received her PhD from [[Purdue University]].<ref>http://www.bgsu.edu/offices/registrar/cat02/Faculty_BGSU_2002.pdf</ref> She was a Fellow of the [[Society for the Scientific Study of Sexuality]], serving as its president between 1985-86.<ref name=ncac>http://www.ncac.org/media/20030305~issues~playboy_US_vs_Playboy.cfm</ref> She was one of the experts to file an [[amicus brief]] in ''[[United States v. Playboy Entertainment Group]]''.<ref name=ncac/>

